# Worktree agents resolve dacli to the worktree's tracked .dacli (a stale HEAD snapshot), not the shared workspace: their own agent file is absent so dacli commit can't attribute them, dacli task check/done edits the stale task file, and notes/events land in the isolated .dacli invisible to root until merge. Discovered running parallel worktree agents for 017-020; agent a-74fbyvmpb0 filed it as intended issue #1 and worked around attribution by copying its agent file in. Fix: resolve the workspace to the outermost real .dacli (git-common-dir) even from a worktree, OR keep run-scoped .dacli state in the shared root. Also: internal/cli tests read DACLI_AGENT from the process env, so a spawned agent's token leaks in and fails project-add tests — add a TestMain that clears it.
